<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="id_rectum_digt"><title>tutor</title><page id="dc6ca3cd68ae4586b8ba18667632a9ab"><question id="q1"><body><p id="acb51039b29c74ced98ce99386fcc1458">Which portion of the large intestine is located directly inferior to the ileocecal valve?</p></body><multiple_choice shuffle="true" select="single" id="bebb457264be4ccd99b3d7cc70750945" labels="false"><choice value="A">Appendix</choice><choice value="B">Sigmoid colon</choice><choice value="C">Cecum</choice><choice value="D">Rectum</choice></multiple_choice><part id="i621899171ffa4e5ba696453ce5b81a7d"><skillref idref="id_lgintestine_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="0"><feedback><p id="afe71392201e7402685c38525214bd08d">Incorrect. The appendix attaches to the segment of the large intestine that is directly inferior to the ileocecal valve.</p></feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback><p id="ac70d51ce241c4b9ea6f5daaa4e7d1e74">Incorrect. The sigmoid colon joins the rectum at the pelvis near the third sacral vertebrae.</p></feedback></response><response match="C" score="10"><feedback><p id="ae28f73e4a0fa493ea9bed1be82febcd6">Correct. The cecum is a small sack like region that is inferior to the ileocecal valve.</p></feedback></response><response match="D" score="0"><feedback><p id="ae7db994ca8cf46409d898f8887c9f9e7">Incorrect. The rectum is the second to most inferior portion of the large intestine.</p></feedback></response></part></question></page></assessment>
